AB  - Many manufacturing industries, including the computer industry, have seen large increases in productivity growth rates and have experienced a reduction in average establishment size. A vintage capital model is introduced which can account for this fact. It is shown that a rise in the rate of technological change decreases average plant size; that is, the level of innovation affects firm size. Smaller plants are not more innovative, as has been suggested, but industries with more innovation, as measured by productivity growth, have smaller plants. Journal of Economic Literature Classification Numbers: D2, O3.
ER  - 
